This paper discusses the development of a performance portable molecular dynamics framework, which involves optimizing code for parallelism and scalability. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including computer engineering (cs.CE), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), modeling and simulation (cs.MS), software engineering (cs.SE), and scientific computing (cs.SC).
